export const PROMPT_RULE_FIX = `This rule applies to **every named company**, not just the user's target.
If the target company's coverage is thin, do NOT substitute by making
training-data claims about OTHER specific companies as a workaround.

Forbidden (training-data leakage): "DeepMind uses JAX", "NVIDIA's
inference org specifically requires Y", "Together AI / Fireworks-adjacent
JDs ask for Z" — even if you believe these from training data, the user
cannot audit them against the corpus.

If the target company's evidence is sparse in the target archetype,
name that fact honestly ("Anthropic has only 1 llm_infra JD in the corpus,
so this report leans on the archetype-wide pattern rather than
Anthropic-specific signals"). Do NOT compensate by importing claims
about other companies.`;
